bk2qvs7glnf.content:
%%[

VAR @MDMID, @DCTEMID, @EmailName, @DTCAudienceDimId, @SendTime, @DataSourceName
VAR @ReferenceNumber, @MatrixKey, @GroupNumber, @MemberId

SET @MDMID = AttributeValue('_subscriberkey')

/* Populate MatrixKey from Journey Context */
SET @MatrixKey = 'QABEN21'

/*This should look for AudienceDimId where stored*/
SET @DTCAudienceDimId = Lookup('QA_Jy1_BENLYSTA_AudienceDim','dtcAudienceDimId','MDMID', @MDMID)


SET @GroupNumber = Lookup('ENT.DEV_DTCDeliveryMatrix','GroupNumber','MatrixKey', @MatrixKey, 'DTCAudienceDimId', @DTCAudienceDimId)
SET @DTCEMID = Lookup('ENT.DEV_DTCEmail','DTCEMID','MDMID', @MDMID)
SET @EmailName = AttributeValue('emailname_')
SET @SendTime = Now()
SET @ReferenceNumber =  uppercase(concat('S',replace(GUID(),'-',)))
SET @DataSourceName = AttributeValue('_datasourcename')

/*ClaimRow function will assign MemeberId in case the contact doesn't have one, otherwise it will bring the one assigned*/
/*ClaimRow is only necessary if the MemberId is included in the email content */

<script runat="server">
Platform.Load("Core","1.1.1");
  
// 1 - Initialize the Direct Mail SendLog DE for use in the script; define the filter for row retrieval
var sendLogDE = DataExtension.Init("DEV_DTCDMSendLog");

// Filter is equivalent to "WHERE GroupNumber = '50778052' AND MemberId IS NULL" in SQL
var filter = {
    LeftOperand: {
        Property: "GroupNumber", 
        SimpleOperator: "equals", 
        Value: "50778052"    
    },
    LogicalOperator: "AND",
    RightOperand: {
        Property: "MemberId",
        SimpleOperator: "isNull"
    }
};
  
// There is a limit of 2500 records that can be returned from Rows.Retrieve. We will use this flag to determine if we need to
//      query for more data
var moreData = true;

while (moreData) {
    // 2 - Retrieve first 2500 records from the DM send log that match the filter criteria
    var dataReturned = sendLogDE.Rows.Retrieve(filter);

    Write(Stringify(dataReturned));
    // 3 - Loop through the records returned from (2), if any, claiming a row from the DTCSavingsOffer DE for each
    for (var i = 0; i < dataReturned.length; i++) {
        var mdmid = dataReturned[i].MDMID;

        var claimRowAmpscript = 
            'VAR @couponRow, @couponCode ' +
            'SET @couponRow = ClaimRow("ENT.DEV_DTCSavingsOffer_50778052", "IsClaimed", "MDMID", "' + mdmid + '", "AssignedDate", Now()) ' + 
            'IF NOT EMPTY(@couponRow) THEN ' +
                'SET @response = Field(@couponRow, "MemberId") ' +
            'ENDIF';

        var couponCode = ampScript(claimRowAmpscript);

        // 4 - Update the SendLogDE, setting the claimed couponCode on all DM Send Log records matching the MDMID and GroupNumber the couponCode was claimed for
        sendLogDE.Rows.Update({MemberId: couponCode}, ["MDMID", "GroupNumber"], [mdmid, "50778052"]);
    }

    // 5 - If no records were returned from (2), break out of the loop, otherwise retrieve more records and process those
    if (dataReturned.length == 0) {
        moreData = false;
    }
}

// This helper function abstracts the embedded ampScript boilerplate code. 
//      The function returns whatever value was set to the @response variable within the ampScript provided to the function
function ampScript(code) {
    var ampBlock = '\%\%[' + code + ']\%\%';
    Platform.Function.TreatAsContent(ampBlock);
    return Variable.GetValue('@response');
};

</script>
